[Jupyter notebook is here!](https://github.com/mchchoi/CS2024)
Recently I read from Twitter about reservoir sampling and the Gumbel max trick. This is my very own attempt to reproduce some of  the basic results from scratch.

#### Formal reference:

[Lost Relatives of the Gumbel Trick (ICML 2017)](https://t.co/1DVCkwnU59)
[Github](https://github.com/matejbalog/gumbel-relatives)

[A* Sampling (NIPS 2014)](https://arxiv.org/abs/1411.0030)

[Perturbation, Optimization and Statistics (NIPS 2013 workshop)](http://www.cs.toronto.edu/~dtarlow/pos13/)


#### Blog reference:

[Estimating means in a finite universe](http://timvieira.github.io/blog/tag/reservoir-sampling.html)

[Gumbel Machinery](https://cmaddis.github.io/)

[Algorithms Every Data Scientist Should Know: Reservoir Sampling](http://blog.cloudera.com/blog/2013/04/hadoop-stratified-randosampling-algorithm/)

[Priority Sampling](http://blog.smola.org/post/1078486350/priority-sampling)

[The Gumbel-Max Trick for Discrete Distributions](https://hips.seas.harvard.edu/blog/2013/04/06/the-gumbel-max-trick-for-discrete-distributions/)

http://blog.geomblog.org/2005/10/priority-sampling.html
